						            	(AP)", "subject": "Digital Fairness Act, Digital Services Act, Digital Markets Act, Digital Omnibus", "cabinet_member": "Werner Stengg, Fausto Matos", "minutes_url": "https://ec.europa.eu/transparencyinitiative/meetings/exportmeetings.do?doc=d668227f-d096-4bcc-ad4a-abb50c81bf8f&host=no", "source_url": "https://ec.europa.eu/transparencyinitiative/meetings/meeting.do?host=8507138f-6be3-4068-9645-5b40bfa5b31f&page=1", "actor_id": "COM_00006A324DF6", "commissioner_name": "Henna Virkkunen", "commissioner_portfolio": "tech sovereignty, security and democracy in the second von der Leyen Commission", "host_id": "8507138f-6be3-4068-9645-5b40bfa5b31f", "meeting_type": "cabinet", "id": "3170807a79360518", "minutes_subject": "Digital Fairness Act, Digital Services Act, Digital Markets Act, Digital Omnibus", "points_raised": "Skyscanner presented their views on the existing regulatory framework. Skyscanner in particular raised concerns about the possible limitations to recommendation systems and personalized customer experience, highlighting the importance of ensuring consistent enforcement throughout the Union. Skyscanner expressed their views on the DSA and emphasized concerns regarding obligations put on intermediary services and, in particular, VLOPs. Obligations on VLOPs should be commensurate with the risks they carry. Moreover, Skyscanner highlighted the importance of the DMA to ensure open and contestable digital markets and raised concerns about bias in AI-powered recommendation systems. Lastly, Skyscanner shared their opinion on the digital omnibus and underlined the importance of avoiding overlaps in consumer regulations and fostering simplification. The Commission representatives took note of the comments made by Skyscanner.", "conclusions": null, "ares_number": null, "transparency_register_ids": ["467615113800-87", "600324619861-95"], "commission_representatives": [{"name": "(s):", "function": null}, {"name": "Fausto Matos", "function": "Member of