points_raised:
- Booking.com:
- stressed its great interest in the ongoing simplification exercises, especially as far as the digital Omnibus is concerned;
- stressed the need to look, in particular, into the relationships between different legal instruments (e.g., DMA, GDPR, AI Act);
- emphasized its constructive approach when it comes to implementing laws such as the DSA, DMA or AI Act;
- expressed the hope that the effects of any EU-level measures taken in the context of the current transatlantic negotiations will be carefully assessed to avoid unwanted side effects on European companies. The Commission representative thanked Booking.com for the information provided.

